messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Yeah, I need police at, uh... Where the heck am I? 291 Watertown Street immediately. We just had bullets fired.
Who shot?
I don't know. Someone out the window.
Out the window of what?
Out the window of the shop.
All right. Do you need an ambulance, too?
Yes, potential hit. Shots fired! Shots fired. 291 Watertown Street.
All right. Stay on the line with me. They're on the way. What happened there? Who was shot?
I don't know. I just heard banging.
Are you in the building?
I am in the building. I work here. There are bullets all over the place. I do have a weapon on me. I have not fired.
How many people are in the building?
No one's firing now. I don't see anyone hurt, but I have two people here. Two women are with me here.
Do you know how many people are in the building total?
There's three on the jewelry side, where the shooting came from, and then I don't know who's on the other side.
You're in Christophori jewelry?
Yes, yes.
All right. I'm going to stay on the line with you until they get there. Are you guys in a safe spot?
I don't know. I don't think so. They shot right through the window.
From inside or outside?
From outside. From the outside.
Are you with the other two people, sir?
Yes, I am. They're both talking.
And you didn't see who shot?
No, but I have cameras here.
Did you see anyone else in the area before this happened?
No, there was a suspicious individual here earlier, but...
All right. Tell me when they get there.
Okay, I can hear them coming.
I can hear them, too, but I'm not going to hang up until you're actually with them, okay?
Here's the police. Can you please check her, please?
Is that an officer, sir?
Yes, there's an officer here.
Okay, can I call my other partner? He's in another location.
Yes, thank you. Bye.
